r the bearers of various religious traditions. Against images of backwardness and heteronomy that are so often associated with religious clothing, it shows the complexity and contingency of processes of consideration and negotiation in everyday vestimentary decision-making situations. Jacqueline Grigo shows that religious clothing is not just an expression of social control or marker of religious belonging or difference - much more, in diverse ways it supports the construction of identity and the social orientation of the self.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aClothing and dressxReligious aspects. 0aClothing and dressxSocial aspects. 0aHuman bodyxReligious aspects. 0aHuman bodyxSocial aspects. 0aSocial SciencesxPsychologyxPsychology, other. 4aDifferenz. 4aFashion Studies. 4aIdentität. 4aKulturanthropologie. 4aMode. 4aReligion. 4aReligionssoziologie. 4aReligionswissenschaft. 4aSchweiz. 4aSoziologie. 70(DE-588)4031011-50(DE-627)1041810280(DE-576)208990089aKleidung2gnd 70(DE-588)4049396-90(DE-627)1061871550(DE-576)209081880aReligion2gnd 70(DE-588)4049420-20(DE-627)1061870820(DE-576)209081988aReligionssoziologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4296178-60(DE-627)1041645490(DE-576)210985100aReligiöser Pluralismus2gnd 70(DE-588)4354651-10(DE-627)1812596050(DE-576)211562815aReligiöse Identität2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aCultural Anthropology.  aDifference.  aFashion Studies.  aIdentity.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.  aSociology of Religion.  aSociology.  aSwitzerland.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE 